"{\"uid\": \"thelineofbestfit.com-news-adele-pauses-munich-concert-to-screen-womens-100m-final-at-olympics\", \"text\": \"On Saturday evening, during her ten-night residency at Messe M\\u00fcnchen, Munich,Adelepaused her show to watch the women's 100m final.  Following her Las Vegas residency, Adele has taken her show to Munich, with a brand new set including the likes of \\\"I will Be Waiting,\\\" \\\"All I Ask,\\\" \\\"Chasing Pavements,\\\" and a cover of Bob Dylan's \\\"Make You Feel My Love\\\". On Saturday (3 August), she paused her show and displayed the Olympic women's 100m final on the venue's big screens.  Adele halts her show in Munich to display the Women's 100m Final at the#Olympics.pic.twitter.com/98n9SrLGj5  Last month,The Killers paused their headline show at The O2in London to show the final moments of England's match against the Netherlands in the Euro 2024 semifinals. After England scored a goal in the 90th minute, confetti cannons erupted and the band went straight into playing the unofficial English national anthem, \\\"Mr. Brightside\\\".  Adele's residency in Munich began on 2 August and will end on 31 August. For more information, visitadele.com.  Get the Best Fit take on the week in music direct to your inbox every Friday\"}"